                  <span class="">[245] ...But in a communist society these leadership and reward practices have definite social-structural consequences. They create and maintain stable networks of identification and allegiances.
[246-249]讲social stability and legitimacy in communist states时从两个层面强调network。
一是上层和积极分子之间的荫庇关系，减少集体行动可能；二是在现有规则里玩得开的人不会想改变规则，也即每个人在工厂制度...</span>
                <p class="pl">
                  <span class="">2016-11-16 20:56</span>
                  
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="all hidden" style="display:none" >
                [245] ...But in a communist society these leadership and reward practices have definite social-structural consequences. They create and maintain stable networks of identification and allegiances.<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>[246-249]讲social stability and legitimacy in communist states时从两个层面强调network。<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>一是上层和积极分子之间的荫庇关系，减少集体行动可能；二是在现有规则里玩得开的人不会想改变规则，也即每个人在工厂制度里都可以bend rules，体会到非正式玩法的好处，并给人一种自己冲击了该system的虚幻满足感，不会去考虑更多abstract issues of justice and equality in a political way。除了这两个原因外，第三个原因是paternalism。<div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div><div class="middle"><img src="https://img3.doubanio.com/view/page_note/large/public/p40253221-1.jpg" alt="总结"><br><span class="pic-title">总结</span></div><div style="padding-bottom:1em;"></div>要是格式原教旨主义者α老师看到我这么中英文字符夹杂地狂乱地记笔记他应该会当机立断停掉我下月工资吧
